tip.text: Waffle with pandan ice-cream and gula Melaka sauce..Delightful! 👍🏻😋
Specially curated concoction. Cocktails are expensive but the entire experience is worth the try. Will be back! Cheers!
Awesome live band 👍🏻

formattedAddress: 3D River Valley Road #01-08 Clarke Quay (Clarke Quay RIver)

tip.text: Inattentive crews. Ordered gizzard, lamb, pork belly, shisamo, squids, salmon belly and few mains. Almost everything we ordered tasted extremely salty. 😖

venue.name: Bangoya Yakitori & Kyushiyaki Izakaya 晚小屋

tip.text: Wouldn't recommend the Peter Pandan. No doubt it's photogenic but the jackfruit overpowered the taste of ice cream and pancake. Chai latte which comes in unique presentation is worth a try :)
Good that they've doubled up the size of their macaron now but thumbs down to their unfriendly crew. No smile, looking at his phone when I'm placing my order and quite ignorant! 😒

formattedAddress: 16, Jalan 2/109E, Desa Business Park, Taman Desa,
location.address: 16, Jalan 2/109E, Desa Business Park, Taman Desa,

formattedAddress: Jaya One (Lot 77-1, Block E), Jalan Universiti
location.address: Jaya One (Lot 77-1, Block E), Jalan Universiti

tip.text: A good place to get your sugar cravings fixed but don't expect too much on their coffee. My latte was disappointing but it's your type of cuppa if you like your Americano in fruity note :)
Egg & bacon bagel taste good though I had difficulties cutting as it was too crunchy on the outside. Would suggest barista to be more careful to avoid overheated milk. Thumbs up for environment 👍🏻
Pork lovers would want to try out their Porkzilla burger which is good for sharing for 2. Food items are reasonably priced and environment is good for a chill hangout too. Would def return :)

formattedAddress: 72A, Jalan Tasik Utama 7 (Medan Niaga Tasik Damai)

tip.text: Cozy homely hideout with good coffee. I really love their eggplant pesto panini and pumpkin choc cake. Will definitely be back for more. Great job guys! 👍🏻😊 Keep it going!! 💪🏻💪🏻💪🏻
This place needs so much improvement or else it's going down in no time. The shisamo that came was pathetic. Sushi on belt weren't fresh but pricing are on par with Umaiya. Staff was friendly though.

formattedAddress: Puchong Batu Dua Belas, Selangor, Selangor

tip.text: From food to service, almost everything in this little sushi restaurant is top notch. I'm really impressed 😃👍
Unlimited toppings when you order their Signature coconut ice-cream available only at this branch 😋
Personally love the Raven blend which leaves a pleasant aftertaste upon each sip of my latte. Friendly barista and cozy interior would win hearts of many :)

formattedAddress: E-01-02, Block E, Plaza Mont Kiara 2, Jalan Kiara
location.address: E-01-02, Block E, Plaza Mont Kiara 2, Jalan Kiara

tip.text: Fresh made pasta adds as a plus point!
Decent food with reasonable pricing. Would probably return for their 'Hungry Belly' and signature pork ribs with peanut sauce. Love their Rambutan breezer and mango & lime breezer too 👍
Good selections of home baked cakes, pies and cupcakes. Place is quiet and cozy. They serve Sumatran Madhelling for espresso based coffees. Dessert lovers would love it here :)
Single shot espresso for long  black & latte tasted mild for single origin Brazil beans. Try double shot if you prefer stronger coffee. In house tiramisu is pretty good. Thumbs up for cozy interior 👍
Decent coffee. Minimalist design & wonderful hospitality from friendly owners out stands this cafe from the rest around this area. Purpose of no wifi to encourage reading. Much love for this place 😍
Seriously rich' hot chocolate is a real deal 😍
Generous amount of ingredients topped on a bed of fluffy vinegar rice. Not one of the best but definitely one of most value for money chirashi don :)

formattedAddress: 4-2, Jalan Telok Gadong (Off Jalan Klang Lama)

tip.text: German sausage, sautéed mushroom, fluffy scramble eggs with sides of muesli bread and salad with sesame dressing make a wholesome big breakfast. All for only RM22 :)
You can never get enough of Mofo deluxe chocolate. So chocolicious 😋 espresso based coffees are pretty decent too 😊

There are still much space for improvement. Coffee tasted burnt. Sautéed mushroom was overly sweet. The only nice thing here is the cranberry poppy seed bread. Was tempted to ask for an extra slice :p
Love how I could personalized the sushi rolls here. Prices are really reasonable too. Practical for a sushi lover like me :)
Mushroom Affairs is one of a kind. A must order for mushroom lovers 🍄🍄🍄
Love the grilled salmon, sautéed vegetables & mashed potatoes albeit salmon was a lil overcooked.  Everything on the plate complement each other. Perfect glass of iced latte. Excellent hospitality 😃
Salted egg bitter gourd is the bomb! 👍😋
Flavour of Cajun chicken pizza was good. The only thing lacking is the crust. Doesn't live up to the term, "thin crust" and it was a lil soggy. However, fantastic serving team. Would be back! :)
Shepherd's pie was below expectation. Meat gravy was a lil too sweet. Latte was alright. Strong but lacking of nice aftertaste. Parking is a hassle here. May consider to return.
Must try the best-seller, Meteor. It's like eating Ferrero Rocher in the form of cake 😋😋

formattedAddress: GK11, Empire Shopping Gallery, Jalan SS 16/1
location.address: GK11, Empire Shopping Gallery, Jalan SS 16/1

tip.text: Monthly routine to come here just for the salmon head in kimchi soup which is good for sharing for 2. Prices for set menu are very reasonable for the portion you get. Much love for this place :)
1st tried their signature dessert when they were newly open a few years back and it tasted heavenly. Anticipated for the dessert last night but the feeling is gone. One of the waiter was rather rude😟
BBQ chicken was too sweet.  Generous toppings on meatball pizza and winner for the dine is Classic New York. Would return for more most probably :)
Pretty nice environment. Love the cakes, hummingbird especially. Coffee with smooth froths. Awesome cappuccino! Flat white a lil lacking of coffee aroma. Friendly owners, Joavnne and Cody :)
Came here twice and failed to try their famous Apple Crumble bingsu. So so disappointed😟 tried their chocolate fudge, marble cheesecake and vanilla iced latte instead. Nothing great to shout about😕
Value for money Vietnamese cuisine. Love the mixed grill with self-service rice noodle wrap concept and sugar cane prawn especially. Friendly boss and workers :)
Love the ambience. Nice place for a catchup session. Service was great. Asked to change my chicken dish because it tasted burn and they apologized for it. Not really impressed with the food though.

venue.name: Svago Cucina e Musica & Limoncello Italian Bistro & Bar

tip.text: Absolutely fresh sashimi, tempura prawn was fried to perfection, doesn't taste oily. Most importantly, friendliest and top class customer service. Would definitely return albeit price is a lil steep:)

formattedAddress: P1-02, Level 1 Podium, Plaza33 (1 Jalan Kemajuan, Seksyen 13)

tip.text: You would definitely love the salt beef hash pie if you love the salt beef hash from Nutmeg. Pie crust thickness was just nice, and not soggy despite having a generous amount of filling inside :)

formattedAddress: F-13A Bangsar Village, 1 Jalan Telawi Satu, Bangsar Baru
location.address: F-13A Bangsar Village, 1 Jalan Telawi Satu, Bangsar Baru

tip.text: Thick cut slices of fresh sashimi at only SGD8. So good 👍👍👍
Love love the interior here. 😍 Bento at reasonable price of RM23 and 120 kinds of sushi to select from. A place that I would definitely return :)
Apple of my eye is moist and not overly sweet. The almond and pastry on top the cake gives a crunchy texture and strong buttery aroma. Best paired with their intense ice latte :)

formattedAddress: B-G-3A Block B, Oasis Square, Jalan PJU 1A/7A Ara Damansara
location.address: B-G-3A Block B, Oasis Square, Jalan PJU 1A/7A Ara Damansara

tip.text: Love both 'Dark Side' and 'Purple Rage'. Crepe thickness was perfect for a satisfying mouthfeel and both crepes weren't overly sweet. Would def return for more! 😋👍👍
Had a really bad dining experience! Mushroom and French onion soup were a total let down. Mushroom is made from instant pack, onion soup was so watery and that side potato tasted burn! So bad!!!👎👎👎

formattedAddress: 50, Ground Floor, Jalan USJ 10/1B (USJ Taipan Triangle)

tip.text: Almost everything is good here. Very flavourful dishes. Set meal may be too huge for a small eater. I suggest order one set meal and add on a rice of you come in a pair :)

venue.name: Fong Lye Taiwan Restaurant (蓬莱茶房)

tip.text: Fresh sashimi, perfect sized sushi with compact rice granules and amazing green tea :)
Nitro coffee tasted fizzy and fruity. Apam balik waffle disappointed me a lil as it wasn't value for money. RM11 for 2 pieces of waffle which tasted bland. Not impressive :/
Valuable set lunch at RM25 inclusive of a drink, appetizer and a main dish. Chose the salted beef fettuccine and it was below expectation. Would be good if the pasta is a bit more flavourful. :)
Lamb shepherds pie is highly recommended. Excellent coffee and hot chocolate with cozy environment. Would definitely return :)

formattedAddress: B-01-06, Plaza Damas 3, Jalan Sri Hartamas 1
location.address: B-01-06, Plaza Damas 3, Jalan Sri Hartamas 1

tip.text: Noodle soup with tomato and meatball, fried mushroom and braised duck egg. Superb!! 😋
BBQ rice ball and octopus so yumehhh!!! 🍘🐙😋
Looks deceiving but taste mediocre. Waffle was a bit dry and hard. Would be nicer if there were more dark chocolate drizzle and portion is just nice for 2 person sharing :)
Was shocked to receive a complimentary tiramisu dessert upon paying the bill even after I had my dish replaced when I complain my chicken was undercooked earlier. Customer service at its best 👍
Eggs Benedict w/ salmon on onion scones was delish 😋 Pretty cosy environment and they're currently renovating the 3rd floor to rent out as event space. New favourite cafe to add on the list 😊
4-hour-smoked chicken was juicy & succulent but not one of the best in town. In short, items in the menu are pretty limited and price a lil on the higher side. Would consider to revisit :)
Taste is fine but there's too much corn in the soup and why would anyone serve the bread in the soup? It makes the bread soggy and I had a hard time eating it since it's soggy. 😒
Great pair of intense iced cafe latte  and smooth shisha. Furnitures are of unique designs at all outlets but seriously, the ergonomic of the furnitures are't comfy for a long sit.

formattedAddress: Level G1, Block A1, Solaris Dutamas
location.address: Level G1, Block A1, Solaris Dutamas

tip.text: This place is really pretty at night with the lights hanging. Quite a no. of plug points upstairs which makes it a nice place to be at when you're rushing for a dateline :) Keep calm & have a cuppa (:
Chicken Schnitzel was pretty good. Breast meat was tender with nicely coated breadcrumbs and flavourful mashed potatoes. Can be shared if you're a small eater :)
Lunch set is affordable for students at below RM15 and comes with side dishes. Pork rib BBQ is the bomb! 😋

venue.name: Da Sa Rang Korea BBQ Restaurant

tip.text: The good reviews are so 2011. Quality has definitely deteriorated badly because 4 person had the worst pancakes by far in their lives. Unpleasant sourness and tasted too flourish!! 👎
黑 chocolate ice-cream is awfully chocolicious. So delectable! 😋

formattedAddress: #02-18, The Star Vista (1 Vista Exchange Green)

tip.text: Two things I would never miss when I'm here. Raven cold brew and their so moist and delicious Hummingbird cake. Best of both world 😊
Curry mushroom & bacon panini is a must try! Value for money. Coffee's acidity is an acquired taste. A good place for brunch nevertheless with plentiful choices of pastries :)
Bon voyage. You'll be missed👋[6th September 2014]

formattedAddress: 6-G, Garden Wing, Sunsuria Avenue (Persiaran Mahogani, Kota Damansara PJU5)

tip.text: Food not up to standard for the price paid. Most importantly, sashimi is not defrosted properly. Once is enough. Would never return again. 👎
Better than Bangsar branch in terms of space and environment. Be warned! You'll get addicted eating their ice-cream especially of those premium flavours. Once is never enough. Nuff said!! 🍦😋
Pork rib hot pot was alright. Not something that I would crave for. Remember to ask for level 1 spiciness if you can't take spicy food.
Yoghurt Royale is the most intriguing dessert I'd ever tasted. Not a fan of dairy product but this is not bad, not bad at all 😊
Awesome not-so-noisy place to chill out with OK shisha, good value food and gourmet coffee all under one roof. 👍
Delish Danish pastries and pretty quiet and nice environment. :)
Thick and flavourful broth. Ramen cooked al-dente. What more could I ask for? 😋
Brownie with ice cream is chocolicious 😋 In love with the cosy environment too 😍

venue.name: Da Sa Rang Korea BBQ Restaurant
Ikan Bakar 烧鱼屋饮食中心
